Several '''Sarcophagi''' are found in the [[Jalsavrah Pyramid]] during the [[Pyramid Plunder]] [[minigame]]. Opening a closed sarcophagus gives [[strength]] [[experience]] and has a chance of awakening a [[mummy]] which will attack the [[player]] that searched the sarcophagus.

Opened sarcophagi can be searched, which will give an artefact which can be sold to [[Simon Templeton]]. The chance of successfully opening a sarcophagus is affected by the player's current strength level.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1405564579351040000|date=17 June 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.is/AGsr9|archivedate=17 June 2021|quote=Yes, your current Strength level does affect that.}}

Because most players in the Pyramid Plunder minigame are focused on [[thieving]] experience, and because the mummy is quite strong, these sarcophagi are rarely opened.

